#SkodaSuperstars

As a kid, I used to sit by the window, dreaming of faraway places I saw in books and postcards.
I promised myself that one day, I’d turn those dreams into reality.
With determination and a backpack, I started small—weekend trips, writing, clicking pictures.
Slowly, brands noticed, and my passion turned into a profession.
Today, I get paid to travel the world, telling stories through my lens and words.
Every journey reminds me that dreams do come true- one step, one mile at a time.

latestPosts.caption:
Going to Paris – A Dream Turned into Reality

Going to Paris wasn’t just a trip; it was a symbol of everything I had worked for, dreamed of, and believed in. I remember the countless times I had imagined standing in front of the Eiffel Tower, walking through the charming streets, and feeling the magic of the city—but for the longest time, it felt like a distant dream.

The day I finally set foot in Paris, it wasn’t just about the beautiful sights; it was about the journey that got me there. Every late night, every challenge, every moment of doubt had led to this moment. As I stood there, taking it all in, I felt overwhelmed with gratitude—for the struggles that shaped me, the hard work that paid off, and the realization that dreams do come true.

Paris was more than just a destination; it was proof that when you believe in yourself, anything is possible. And that feeling? That was my biggest win.

#wearyourwins

latestPosts.caption:
My Goal: Embracing Motherhood Without Mom Guilt

As a first-time mom, my biggest goal is to be present for my baby while also taking care of myself—without feeling guilty. Mom guilt creeps in so easily, but I’m learning that a happy and healthy mom means a happy baby.

Steps I’m Taking:

✔ Prioritizing Quality Over Quantity – Instead of feeling guilty about every minute apart, I focus on making our time together meaningful and full of love.

✔ Accepting Help & Setting Boundaries – I remind myself that asking for help doesn’t make me any less of a mom. It allows me to recharge and be my best self.

✔ Letting Go of Perfection – I no longer stress over every small thing. My baby needs love, not perfection, and I’m enough just as I am.

✔ Taking Care of Myself Too – Whether it’s a short walk, a cup of coffee in peace, or a moment to breathe, I remind myself that self-care isn’t selfish—it’s necessary.

Each day, I’m learning to give myself grace, patience, and kindness, just as I do for my little one. Motherhood is a journey, and I’m embracing it one step at a time!

#WomenOfActions

latestPosts.caption:
Lovely evening at The ICONIC Taj Mahal Palace , Mumbai.🌸

Taking my parents to The Taj Mahal Palace, Mumbai for a meal with my first salary was a truly special and emotional experience. Ever since I started working, I had dreamt of giving them a small token of gratitude for all their sacrifices, and this felt like the perfect way to do it.

Walking into the grand hotel, seeing their eyes light up with wonder, and watching them enjoy the warm hospitality and delicious food made my heart full. It wasn’t about the luxury—it was about making them feel cherished and showing them how much they mean to me.

We first went to the Sea lounge to enjoy high tea . It was such a beautiful experience to have such amazing delicacies by the sea, with a gorgeous view of the Gateway. We couldn’t believe for a second that we were experiencing this in an extremely busy city.

The Taj lounge blew our minds, we then sat by the pool , enjoyed live music ,and head to Shamiana for dinner.
My parents were blown away by the food and how authentic and vintage the vibes were.

We laughed, reminisced about old times, and for a moment, it felt like life had come full circle, I realized that this moment was worth more than anything money could buy. My parents had always been my biggest supporters, and that evening, as they smiled with pride, I felt like I had given them a tiny piece of the love and care they had showered on me all my life. It was more than just a meal—it was a memory, a moment of pure joy that I will cherish forever.✨🫶

#MyBondWithTaj
